//! At-rest-extension spike — Leg 2 (T0.2.0 pre-task).
//!
//! Validates the `lance::Dataset` + `WrappingObjectStore` integration path
//! for the at-rest sealed-ObjectStore adapter design (per ADR-008
//! amendment 2026-05-XX, pending). Spike scope:
//!
//!   - **Stage A** — identity-wrapper compile + Lance write+read round-trip.
//!     Proves dep stack + WrappingObjectStore trait wiring at compile +
//!     runtime. NO sealing.
//!   - **Stage B** — sealing primitives (K3 KDF, DryocStream as
//!     single-shot, AAD compute) as standalone functions + inline
//!     adversarial unit tests. NO ObjectStore wrapping yet.
//!   - **Stage C** — `SealedObjectStore` wrapping `LocalFileSystem`,
//!     end-to-end sealed write through Lance `Dataset`, on-disk
//!     adversarial assertions. **Read path BLOCKED**: lance-io 0.15's
//!     `LocalObjectReader` bypasses `object_store::ObjectStore` for
//!     local-fs paths (per docs.rs/lance-io/0.15.0/lance_io/local/
//!     struct.LocalObjectReader.html — direct std::fs access for
//!     reads), so `WrappingObjectStore::wrap` does not intercept
//!     manifest / fragment reads. Spike escalation trigger fired
//!     2026-05-XX. Resolution = T0.2.0 plan paragraph iteration 1
//!     selects from Path W'/X'/Y'/Z' (see ADR-008 amendment +
//!     T0.2.0 plan paragraph drafts). Stage C produces the on-disk
//!     evidence (sealed framing + entropy + no PAR1) that confirms
//!     write path is correct; read path needs the path decision
//!     before re-spike.
//!
//! ## Locked decisions consumed by this spike
//!
//! - **AAD scheme** (Finding 2 candidate (c), iteration 3 lock):
//!   `AAD = BLAKE3("vault-at-rest-v1" || file_path_bytes)`. No `version_id`
//!   binding in V0.2; replay-attack residual documented in amendment with
//!   V1.0 revisit trigger.
//! - **KDF** (K3, surfaced + locked at Stage A close):
//!   `at_rest_key = blake3::derive_key("vault memory at-rest sealing v1",
//!   &master_key)`. K3 chosen over K1 (HKDF-SHA256 via new RustCrypto
//!   crate) and K2 (dryoc `crypto_kdf_blake2b`) for single-source-crypto
//!   preservation per ADR-008 line 693, plus uniformity with the AAD
//!   computation already on BLAKE3.
//! - **Sealing granularity** (iteration 3 §3.1): per-file. V0.2
//!   unconditional.
//! - **Sealing shape** (iteration 3 §3.4):
//!   `version_byte (0x01) || granularity_marker (0x00) || dryoc_header (24
//!   bytes) || ciphertext`. 26-byte framing overhead.
//! - **Path #1 cipher** (ADR-008 archive line 681): DryocStream-as-single-
//!   message wrapped per envelope, `Tag::FINAL` on push.
//!
//! Run via:
//!   ```
//!   cargo run -p vault-storage --example at_rest_spike
//!   ```
//! (Requires PROTOC + Strawberry Perl on PATH per ADR-006 / ADR-011.)

